stylometry: Data mining is used in business to find trends. Data is useful facts (about customers) that then can be stored in data warehouses. The information obtained from the data is very beneficial in businessess. One example we've done with data mining - is where we had data of customers - x & y coordinates of their location, their annual orders, and how far away from the warehouses are they was what we needed to find. In general, having data about customers can let you know things like how often they order, how much, etc. This is great in business because the trends can either help you organize your current customers - and make is easier in the selling process; or use those trends to know who wants what, where the demand is coming from, and how much they order - to try and get potential new customers.
